Microsoft aspires to help our customers achieve their own digital transformation, leveraging the power of Microsoft Cloud solutions and services. To this end, Microsoft is investing in a dedicated Customer Success team that will help Microsoft customers successfully adopt Microsoft Cloud solution and services. 
As part of this growth, we are recruiting for a talented CSA Manager to lead a team of deeply technical Cloud Solution Architects (CSA), focused in AI and machine learning, to drive growth of Azure AI Services for a set of Enterprise accounts across different industries . This is an exciting role that will help fuel Azure Customer success through innovation and adoption of data governance. 
Responsibilities 
This represents an exciting opportunity for a Manager to lead a team of deeply technical AI& ML focused CSA's that will help fuel Azure Customer success through innovation and adoption of data governance. 
Key responsibilities include: 
Hire, on-board, develop, coach, mentor and evaluate an AI-focused CSA team, effectively set a clear bar for excellence; build a high performing team that will be diverse and inclusive.Must possess exceptional cross-team collaboration and communication. 
Partner with all required Microsoft stakeholders in WCB and subsidiary to drive CSA role clarity, account coverage, project assignment and effective cross-team collaboration 
Coach and enable your team to accelerate Azure AI projects toproduction, including guidance on architectural design, technical recommendations, hands on development of POCs and MVPs, blocker escalations and technical resource orchestration 
Ensure your team delivers high quality production AI-powered deployments that are resilient and successful and creates re-usable IP / best practices that can be shared and replicated across regions 
Drive operational excellence, including timely consumption opportunity management and high-quality reporting and insights 
Qualifications 
To be considered for this CSA Manager role, we're looking for an individual to offer excellence and competency across a range of areas: 
Professional Expertise 
Experience. 10+ years of experience in technical sales, engineering or consultative delivery services with atleast 3 years in the AI space (required) 
Management.3+ years of experience in people management (required) with preferably managing geographically disperse teams across timezones, as well as gained in other leading software and/or services companies/competitor environment 
Change.7+ years of experience driving change management or technical adoption(required) 
Collaboration.Proven ability to generate trust, build alliances, and orchestrate interdisciplinary teams to the benefit of customers 
Communication.Thought-leader with executive presence, including the ability to hold CxO and BDM level discussions, exceptional interpersonal, verbal, written and presentation skills 
Prior work experience in other software and/or services companies such as Amazon, Google, IBM, Oracle(desired ) 
Technical 
Strong and relevant technical understanding of AI and machine learning, including AI enterprise cloud workloads 
Strong understand of Azure AI Platform (or other AI platform such as AWS, GCP, IBM) â€“ Azure Machine Learning, Azure Cognitive Search, Azure Cognitive Services and Azure Bot Services 
Proven ability to map the customerâ€™s needs to technical solutions 
Ability to stay up to date on new/improved Azure AI and data governance scenarios and workloads 
Empathy, curiosity, and desire to constantly improve, acquire new skills and drive for results 
Demonstrated Technical leadership through prior technical coaching/leadership roles 
Ability to act on Customer Escalation and needs, Unblock the customer through orchestration of right resources at the right time 
Education 
A bachelor's degree in Computer Science, IT, Engineering or related field, or relevant experience highly preferred 
Certification in one or more of the following technologiespreferred:Data Science, Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence 
